boost 2H with Punishing Blade before 2H will likely outperform 1H.<br>
<br>
The reason tripple attack boosts 2H more than 1H is that it only effects the primary hand.  So, for 2H you have a 3:2 or +50% damage output.  For 1H you have a 5:4 or +25% damage output.  That's best case.  If you factor in the chances for double attack and dual wield, 2H gains even more by comparison. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sordail>Sordail</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/03 1:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It depends a great deal on ..</span><hr size=1> Argh!<br>
